explains: adj. 无名的；未命名的；未提及的

sentences.en: Two casualties, as yet unnamed, are still in the local hospital.
sentences.cn: 两个尚不知姓名的伤者仍在当地医院。

sentences.en: Friedman's lengthy report quoted an unnamed source.
sentences.cn: 弗里德曼冗长的报告引用了一个未指明出处的资料。

sentences.en: Perot accused unnamed U.S. officials of covering up the facts.
sentences.cn: 佩罗未指名地谴责美国官员掩盖了事实。
